body:
A duplicate of #1654 with additional commits that automatically address incorrect style, created by [Restyled][]. Since the original Pull Request was opened as a fork in a contributor's repository, we are unable to create a Pull Request branching from it with only the style fixes. The following Restylers [made fixes](https://restyled.io/gh/TokTok/repos/c-toxcore/jobs/1349899): - astyle - clang-format To incorporate these changes, you can either: 1. Merge this Pull Request *instead of* the original, or 1. Ask your contributor to locally incorporate these commits and push them to the original Pull Request
Expand for example instructions ```console git remote add upstream https://github.com/TokTok/c-toxcore.git git fetch upstream pull//head git merge --ff-only FETCH_HEAD git push ```
**NOTE**: As work continues on the original Pull Request, this process will re-run and update (force-push) this Pull Request with updated style fixes as necessary. If the style is fixed manually at any point (i.e. this process finds no fixes to make), this Pull Request will be closed automatically. Sorry if this was unexpected. To disable it, see our [documentation][]. [restyled]: https://restyled.io [documentation]: https://github.com/restyled-io/restyled.io/wiki/Disabling-Restyled --- This change isâ€‚[](https://reviewable.io/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/1764)

Add new feature - topic lock

Group founders can now toggle a topic lock. When the lock is enabled
only the founder and moderators can change the topic. When disabled
anyone can change the topic

Temporarily fix an issue with group DHT announcements

This prevents announce spam that was being caused by a TCP implementation
bug that made the sole testnet tcp relay connection status alternate from
online to offline. This will need to be reverted once we merge with the
mainnet, or when the TCP bug gets fixed

commit.message:
Refactor the way we send packets and remove ugly hack

We now store the plaintext data in the send array and encrypt it on each send attempt.
This prevents us from sending packets from our send array that were encrypted with
an old shared key that the recipient no longer has the means to decrypt. This in
turn allows us to remove the ugly hack where we were keeping he last shared key
around to decrypt recent messages
